  "system": {
    "description": {
      "value": "<p><em><span id=\"ctl00_MainContent_DataListTypes_ctl47_LabelType\">The orcs of Belkzen routinely mix the blood of their enemies with potions they brew to gain some of their foe&rsquo;s strength.</span></em></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><span id=\"ctl00_MainContent_DataListTraits_ctl00_LabelName\"><strong>Requirements</strong></span></p>\n<p><span id=\"ctl00_MainContent_DataListTypes_ctl47_LabelType\">Belkzen</span></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>Benefits</strong></p>\n<p><span id=\"ctl00_MainContent_DataListTypes_ctl47_LabelType\">Twice per day when you brew a potion, you can add some of an enemy&rsquo;s blood to the mixture. When you do, the potion&rsquo;s caster level is treated as 1 higher when you drink it for the purpose of determining the duration of the potion&rsquo;s effects. This ability has no effect if another creature drinks the potion. This trait does not grant the ability to brew potions.</span></p>",
